"Streck N.A., Alberto C.M.","Numerical study of the impact of climate change on the yield of wheat, soybean and maize [Estudo numérico do impacto da mudança climática sobre o rendimento de trigo, soja e milho]",2006,"Pesquisa Agropecuaria Brasileira","41","9",,"1351","1359",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33750805515&partnerID=40&md5=ec0ac7889bf269dd530c601d5491742b","Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Dep. de Fitotecnia, CEP 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil","Streck, N.A., Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Dep. de Fitotecnia, CEP 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil; Alberto, C.M., Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Dep. de Fitotecnia, CEP 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil","The objective of this work was to evaluate through a numerical study the impact of a possible climate change on the yield of wheat, soybean and maize, in Santa Maria, RS. Climate change scenarios were created by doubling CO 2, with different increases in air temperature, and with increases and without increases in rainfall. Yield of the three crops was simulated with models available in the literature. It was concluded that projected climate change will affect wheat, soybean and maize yield in Santa Maria, RS, Brazil. The increase of 2, 3 and 6°C may cancel the benefits of increasing CO 2 on yield of wheat, soybean and maize, respectively.","Agriculture; Food supply; Global warming; Glycine max; Triticum aestivum; Zea mays","Glycine max; Triticum aestivum; Zea mays",,,,,,"Amir, J., Sinclair, T.R., A model of water limitation on spring wheat growth and yield (1991) Field Crops Research, 28, pp. 59-69; Amthor, J.S., Effects of atmospheric CO2 on wheat yield: Review of results from experiments using various approaches to control CO2 concentration (2001) Field Crops Research, 73, pp. 1-34; Andresen, J.A., Alagarswamy, G., Rotz, C.A., Ritchie, J.T., LeBaron, A.W., Weather impacts on maize, so